# fourstatebutton: each press advances 0->1->2->3->0. output copies value1..4;
# led = state/3 (0, 1/3, 2/3, 1). Values kept within +-1.0 so they can be read
# directly off O1.
#   t0 state0 -> output value1 0.1, led 0
#   t1 state1 -> output value2 0.2, led 0.3333
#   t3 state2 -> output value3 0.3, led 0.6667
#   t5 state3 -> output value4 0.4, led 1
#   t7 state0 -> output 0.1, led 0 (wrap)
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[p2b8]

[fourstatebutton]
    button = B1.1
    led    = L1.1
    value1 = 0.1
    value2 = 0.2
    value3 = 0.3
    value4 = 0.4
    output = O1
>>>
@0 expect O1 0.1 tol 1e-4
@0 expect L1.1 0 tol 1e-4
@1 set B1.1 1
@1 expect O1 0.2 tol 1e-4
@1 expect L1.1 0.33333 tol 1e-3
@2 set B1.1 0
@3 set B1.1 1
@3 expect O1 0.3 tol 1e-4
@3 expect L1.1 0.66667 tol 1e-3
@4 set B1.1 0
@5 set B1.1 1
@5 expect O1 0.4 tol 1e-4
@5 expect L1.1 1 tol 1e-4
@6 set B1.1 0
@7 set B1.1 1
@7 expect O1 0.1 tol 1e-4
@7 expect L1.1 0 tol 1e-4
@8 set B1.1 0
